#compdef ublue-update
# Documentation: source-direct extraction from upstream
# ublue-os/ublue-update src/ublue_update/cli.py —
#   main() at lines 183-213 (the argparse.ArgumentParser +
#     6 add_argument calls)
# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30 via gh api.
#
# ublue-update is the **Universal Blue (ublue-os) update
# daemon CLI** — runs system + system-extension + flatpak +
# distrobox-container updates on Bazzite / Bluefin / Aurora /
# Aurora-DX / Bluefin-DX / Bazzite-DX.  Sister tool to R226's
# ujust (the recipe runner that triggers this update flow
# from `ujust update`).
#
# Critical extraction note: ublue-update is a **Python
# argparse-based CLI** (NOT clap/cobra/argh/cmdr).  Simple
# 6-flag set:
#   -f/--force          force manual update, skip checks
#   -c/--check          run update checks and exit
#   -u/--updatecheck    check for updates and exit
#   -w/--wait           wait for transactions to complete
#   --config FILE       use specified config file
#   --system            only run system updates (requires root)
# All 6 are mutually compatible except for some runtime
# behavior at lines 218-220 (`if cli_args.wait: …; os._exit(0)`)
# which exits early if --wait is set, bypassing the other
# update flow.

_arguments -s -S \
  '(-h --help)'{-h,--help}'[show help and exit]' \
  '(-f --force)'{-f,--force}'[force manual update, skipping update checks]' \
  '(-c --check)'{-c,--check}'[run update checks and exit]' \
  '(-u --updatecheck)'{-u,--updatecheck}'[check for updates and exit]' \
  '(-w --wait)'{-w,--wait}'[wait for in-progress transactions to complete, then exit]' \
  '--config=[use the specified config file (default: /etc/ublue-update/ublue-update.toml)]:file:_files -g "*.toml"' \
  '--system[only run system updates (requires root; skips per-user flatpak/distrobox)]'
